The article expresses deep sadness over the passing of Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah, the Amir of Kuwait. The author, believed to be President Donald Trump, extends condolences to the people of Kuwait. Sheikh Sabah was described as a steadfast friend and partner to the United States. The author mentions having recently awarded him the prestigious Legion of Merit, Degree Chief Commander. Sheikh Sabah's 40-year tenure as Foreign Minister and his tireless efforts in mediating disputes in the Middle East are highlighted. The author expresses hope that Gulf nations will come together to honor his legacy and work towards a cooperative future.